		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Oh yeah. Well, the framebuffer area still hasn't changed though. You can DMA 14,233 bytes in a frame, and the frame buffer is 31,104 bytes, so you can almost have the game run at 30fps. I personally would settle for a lower frame rate and resolution for having about 16x the amount of color.

		

